AUTOMATIC WRAPPING MACHINE CO. v. PNEUMATIC SCALE CORPORATION, Inc. NO. 4977. Circuit Court of Appeals, Seventh Circuit. July 27, 1933. Thomas H. Pisher, of Chicago, 111., for' appellant. Ellis Spear, Jr., of Washington, D. C., and William 0. Belt, of Chicago, 111., for ap-pellee.

Before ALSCHÜDER, and EVANS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On motion of counsel for appellant, counsel for appellee consenting, it is ordered, adjudged, and decreed by this court that this appeal be, and the same is hereby, dismissed, with costs.
